      "raw_text": "A general expression of satisfac-\nton over the course pursued in the\nrailroad rate fight is. heard on all\nsides. Levi G. Monroe, secretary OF\nthe chamber Of commerce, today\nsaid that at a committee meeting\nlast night the expression of men,\nbers showed an expectation that\nthe commission would grant Spo-\nkane very substantial relief. The\ncommittee was pleased at the man\nner in which the fight was carried\non by Attorneys A. II. Stephens,\nBrooks Adams and Corporation\nCounsel Geraghty. Mr. Monroe con-\nsiders the evidence gwen by James\nj. Hill in the big merger case.\nwherein he said he could haul\nfreight and make money at $3.50 a\nton, and which was introduced here,\nchincher in favor Of Spokanes\ncomplaint.\n\n\nThe railroads involved in the rate\nfight made by this city must furn-\nish the interstate commerce COM\nmission with detailed information"
